Diagnosis. Male with modified metafemora: their dorsal (anterior in
Fig. 1
) margin in basal half bulging and femur near middle rapidly narrowing distally, posterior (dorsal in
Fig. 1
) surface of femur near middle with large shallow pit; female also has weakly concave dorsal femoral margin in the same region as male, although base of femur is not swollen.

Redescription. Body of male (
Fig. 1
) strongly convex, elongate and relatively slender, with long appendages, BL 1.48 mm ; cuticle moderately glossy, uniformly brown with slightly lighter legs, antennae and palps and darker head (except light supraantennal tubercles); vestiture light brown.

